menu "breadboard: bb_storage_nvs"

config BB_STORAGE_NVS_GET_SCRATCH_MAX
    int "Max bytes for truncated blob reads via the generic bb_storage facade"
    default 512
    help
        When a caller requests fewer bytes (cap) than a stored NVS blob's
        full length via the generic bb_storage_get() facade, the "nvs"
        backend copies through a bounded on-stack scratch buffer of this
        size (no heap). A blob larger than this value that also needs
        truncation returns BB_ERR_NO_SPACE. Does not apply to
        bb_nv_get_str/u8/u16/u32 (the typed accessors read directly into the
        caller's buffer via nvs_get_str/nvs_get_u*, unaffected by this
        limit).

endmenu
